The paper proposes a Genetic-Programming algorithm for evolving Gaussian Process kernels, which is a machine learning technique. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and search algorithms, which are common in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with time-series extrapolation problems, which are related to control and system identification, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves mathematical expressions and modeling, which are common in the sub-category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
